commitResults.messageBody:
Updated UserGuide.md so that all commands are
using the same tags for the same type of data.
UI.java is therefore edited to standardize the
help message.

Modified Book.java to remove synopsis from the
object and add genres. toString() is modified to
display genres.

Implemented the add command to add books to the
resource list. Validated user input for add command.

Changed the naming of taskList to resourceList and
added SysLibException.java. Hence, edited
Command.java, DeleteCommand.java, ListCommand.java,
and Parser.java.

Added tag function to identify and specify the
type of resources added.

Modified parseAddCommand method to be more generic.
Added parsing and validation methods for adding
books.
Update logic and code quality of ListCommand

Added addCommand JUnit tests to AddCommandTest.java.
Updated Book.java and Parser.java.

Added on to the developer guide and included parts
for the add feature.

Added eBook, CD, magazine, eMagazine, newspaper,
and eNewspaper in addition to Book.

Added validation for all resources. Different

commitResults.messageTitle: Add EditCommand feature and update User Guide
commitResults.messageBody:
Librarians may want to update resources due to mistakes or outdated
information

Hence, add a new Edit feature to update the title, author, tag, or
genre and update the Parser with new edit command

Update User Guide with details of new Edit Command

Add tests for EditCommand

In future update:
-Update help message with new Edit Command
-Update genre editing to allow user to edit a specific genre rather
than all of them

Librarians may want to track how long a resource has been in their
care

Hence, add a receivedDate attribute to resource which automatically
takes the current system time. Use current system time in order
to reduce the amount of input a user has to type and it is also
more logical to take the current system time

Update toString() and tests cases accordingly
Fix incorrect return in parser for Status

commitResults.messageTitle: Add CommandResult class and feedbackToUser variable to all commands
commitResults.messageBody:
All commands currently print every statement which may look messy
and hard to get its output message

Hence, instead of printing every string, create a feedbackToUser
string in every Command class and add messages to that variable

CommmandResult then stores feedbackToUser and Parser prints the
final result at the end of command execution
